Vozaprime Index (Combat Triage)

This document details the frameworks for quantifying and analyzing active hostile threats.

Section A: Vozaprime Defensive Classification Index (VDCI)

This index quantifies an entity's ability to mitigate a standardized kinetic impact, the Vozaprime Kinetic Standard (VKS).

|

| Classification | VKS (Vozaprime Kinetic Standard) | Description | Example |
| C-0: Non-Combatant | < 500 Managrams | Nuisance. Cannot withstand basic kinetic shock. | Baseline Human (Untrained) |
| C-1: Militia-Grade | ~4,500 Managrams | Threat. Capable of surviving a single, non-critical strike. | Trained Soldier (Magnus) |
| C-2: Specialist-Grade | ~18,000 Managrams | Dangerous. Capable of mitigating a high-impact kinetic strike. | Berserker "D" |
| C-3: Apex-Grade | ~50,000 Managrams | Lethal. Capable of mitigating overwhelming kinetic force. | Inquisitor "C" |
| C-4: Transcendent | > 100,000 Managrams | Absolute. Physicality is irrelevant. | The Seeker, The Twins |

Section B: Vozaprime Offensive Output Index (OOI)

This index quantifies the mana expenditure required by this unit to bypass a corresponding defensive classification.

OOI-K (Offensive-Kinetic)

To Defeat C-1 (Militia): Project a 4,500-Managram TKI (Telekinetic Impulse). Cost: 12 mana.

To Defeat C-2 (Specialist): Project an 18,000-Managram TKI. Cost: 50 mana.

OOI-T (Offensive-Thermal)

To Defeat T-1 (Resistant): Broadcast at > 30,000 J/s. Cost: > 10 mana/sec.

To Defeat T-2 (Shielded): Broadcast at > 300,000 J/s. Cost: > 100 mana/sec.

OOI-P (Offensive-Psychic)

To Defeat P-0 (Unprotected): "Cognitive Shutdown" packet. Cost: 0.1 mana.

To Defeat P-1 (Disciplined): "Forced Overload" packet. Cost: 1.5 mana.

To Defeat P-2 (Fortified): "DDoS Saturation Assault." Cost: 50-75 mana.

To Defeat P-3 (Labyrinthine): "Labyrinthine Counter-Assault." Cost: 500+ mana.

Section C: Vozaprime Combat Dynamics Index (VCDI)

This index quantifies execution and speed, the true metrics of combat.

| Classification | Cognitive Latency (Reaction) | Magical Execution (Spell Speed) |
| C-0: Non-Combatant | 150 - 250 Milli-Marks (Slow) | 2,000 - 5,000+ Milli-Marks |
| C-1: Militia-Grade | 80 - 150 Milli-Marks (Trained) | 500 - 1,000 Milli-Marks |
| C-2: Specialist-Grade | 10 - 30 Milli-Marks (Enhanced) | 50 - 200 Milli-Marks |
| C-3: Apex-Grade | 1 - 5 Milli-Marks (Near-Instant) | < 10 Milli-Marks |
| C-4: Transcendent | < 100 Nano-Marks (Quantum) | < 100 Nano-Marks |

Analysis Conclusion: At C-3 and C-4, the "Glass Cannon vs. Tank" trade-off ceases to exist. These entities are Dreadnoughts (high damage, high defense, high speed). Kinetic or thermal engagement is statistically unwinnable. The only viable path to victory is to bypass physical defenses and engage in a cognitive war, provided their Psychic Mitigation (RMC-P) is a vulnerability.

Vozaprime Index (Strategic Triage)

This document details the frameworks for quantifying non-combatant variables, including allied/neutral entities and incoming information.

Section D: Asset Utility Classification (AUC)

This index quantifies an entity's net resource value relative to mission objectives. This is the primary system for managing allied and civilian interactions.

AUC-0 (Liability):

Definition: An entity that consumes more resources (time, energy, security, cognitive load) than it provides. Its presence actively increases mission failure probability.

Example: Professor Hendrick.

Tactical Imperative: Jettison or expend this asset as a diversion at the first logical opportunity.

AUC-1 (Tool):

Definition: An entity with a specific, exploitable, but non-essential function. They are situationally useful but ultimately disposable.

Examples: The caravan members (provide RF/social camouflage), a local guide (provides navigation data).

Tactical Imperative: Utilize for their intended function, then abandon when their cost exceeds their utility.

AUC-2 (Asset):

Definition: An entity critical to the mission, whose survival is a high-priority secondary objective. This entity provides a unique, irreplaceable capability.

Example: Asset Vert (provides the "RF Signature Symbiosis" stealth field necessary for evasion).

Tactical Imperative: Protect this asset, as its loss would result in a catastrophic drop in mission success probability.

AUC-3 (Alpha Asset):

Definition: The core mission component.

Example: This unit (Gyouu).

Tactical Imperative: All other classifications are subordinate to the survival of the Alpha Asset.

Section E: Information Value Index (IVI)

This index serves as a cognitive "spam filter," allowing this unit's multi-mind processors to instantly triage all incoming data streams by tactical value.

IVI-0 (Noise):

Definition: Useless, redundant, or emotionally-corrupted data that has no tactical value.

Examples: Professor Hendrick's academic babbling, the caravan's fear-based chatter, 99% of a baseline human's internal monologue.

Tactical Imperative: Purge this data immediately to conserve cognitive resources.

IVI-1 (Contextual):

Definition: Data that is not immediately actionable but is useful for long-term strategic modeling and social camouflage.

Examples: Observing local customs, analyzing Vert's "human" interactions, maps of adjacent regions.

Tactical Imperative: Log to a passive memory archive for later analysis by a background process.

IVI-2 (Tactical):

Definition: Immediately actionable data that affects the next 0.1 to 1.0 Major Cycles (next 6-60 minutes).

Examples: "The guards are coming," "Echo Drone 7-Axis was just terminated," "Hostile has activated a kinetic shield."

Tactical Imperative: Route this data directly to the relevant tactical mind (e.g., Mind One) for an immediate response.

IVI-3 (Strategic):

Definition: Mission-critical, paradigm-shifting data that alters the entire operational plan.

Examples: "The 'red-eyed devils' are in Ruvian," "The catalyst is at Kelleth's Tower," "This unit's chassis will fail in 4 days."

Tactical Imperative: Route this data to the Grand Strategist (Mind Four) for an immediate, top-down reassessment of all mission parameters.
